CMake
-----

targets

generators

commands

The SET command is an inherited command.

The ADD_EXECUTABLE command is not inherited.

The InitialPass method.

The FinalPass method.

Targets represent executables, libraries, and utilities built by CMake:
ADD_LIBRARY, ADD_EXECUTABLE, and ADD_CUSTOM_TARGET commands.

Libraries can be declared to be STATIC, SHARED, MODULE, or left undeclared. 
BUILD_SHARED_LIBS is used to determine if the library should be SHARED or
STATIC.

